/*
  Flag existing notifications as RETURNED

  https://eaflood.atlassian.net/browse/WATER-5334

  We've recently [added a callback url for GovNotify](https://github.com/DEFRA/water-abstraction-system/pull/2383) to
  tell us when a letter is returned to them. We then updated that to [set the status and returned at
  date](https://github.com/DEFRA/water-abstraction-system/pull/2471) on the notification. We can use this information to
  inform users via the UI which notifications have been returned.

  However, this will only tell us about future pings. Notify provides a series of downloadable reports for returned
  letters, which currently go back to June 2023. If we take this information, we can update the status of existing
  notifications to `RETURNED` as well.

  So, this change is a migration built from the data in those reports. Some notifications may have been sent directly
  via the dashboard, so they won't exist in our service. Others might, but the legacy code errored before the notify ID
  could be persisted.

  Either way, it is better than nothing. The only other wrinkle is when we get a ping, we use the current date as the
  value for `returned_at`. This isn't available in the reports, so we have used the report date for the value instead.
*/

-- 1. Update all the notifications using the data provided in the Notify reports
